## Context

This is Task 1 of 11 in the cluster-a-define-solve sub-sprint under master plan `20260430-02-rebuild-design-derivation`. The sprint adds `RESOLVE_CONDITION` as the proof MCP's sixth element type alongside the existing five immutable types (EVIDENCE, RULE, PERMISSION, NECESSARY_CONDITION, RISK).

Architectural constraint: RULE-1 (master plan) — the five existing element types are immutable. Their validation blocks, schemas, and source rules cannot change. ELEMENT_TYPES gets appended to, never reordered.

Universal-shell decision: spec line 22 commits that `problem_anchor` and `ratification` default null on EVERY element type, not just RC. This is the universal-shell pattern. Existing five types do not validate these fields — they simply carry them as null.

